`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
Testing against the actual config JSON (not hardcoded copies) is a contract test — if someone changes `hard.hungerDrainRate` from 1.5 to 1.4 in the JSON, the test catches the spec drift immediately. This is more valuable than a unit test that just verifies `tickHunger(100, 100, 60, 1.5)` because it locks config values to spec expectations.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

